mts.s:
From your WBS and Gantt Chart, estimate how much this project would cost if you were employed.  Use figures presented in class.
 
State in 1-2 paragraphs how you would control for quality.  What measurements would you take in order to make a case that this project was of high quality?
 
List the risks involved in doing this project at each step.  Accompany each with a statement about how you would mitigate risk.

1.0 Initiating
	1.1 Describing the Project
		a. Redesigning a UCI club website
	1.2 Identifying key stakeholders
		a. Current and future club officers, members, sponsors, donors, outside organizations
	1.3 Creating a business case
	1.4 Identifying scope

2.0 Planning
	2.1 Hold team meeting
	2.2 Prepare team contract
		a. Agree on responsibilities and consequences
	2.3 Prepare scope statement
		a. Identify and finalize scope of the project
			i. Redesign layout and aesthetics
			ii. Implement new features (i.e. Calendar, online payments, chatbox)
	2.4 Prepare WBS
	2.5 Create Gantt chart and prepare schedule
		a. Visualize what time slots team available
		b. Set meeting times for preparing execution (i.e. when to design, test etc)
	2.5 Identify, discuss and prioritize risks
		a. Unable to finish project in time
		b. Lack of mutual understanding with customers
	2.6 Interviewing stakeholders and customers
		a. Hold meetings with current club officers
			i. What aspects needs improvement? What are current problems?
	2.7 Plan execution
		a. Plan out what needs to be implemented
		b. Decide which requirements are feasible and can be completed in the given time

3.0 Executing
	3.1 Whiteboard design or storyboarding
		a. Weekly team meetings for design sessions
		b. Repeat using whiteboard until designs are more finalized
	3.2 Create mockups
		a. Use Balsamiq to visualize design
	3.3 Testing
		a. Run by current officers and potential users
		b. Test on a few members? (i.e. Prototyping)

4.0 Monitoring and Controlling
	4.1 Progress meetings
		a. Weekly team meetings
		b. Constant team communication via email and phone
	4.2 Generate feedback from stakeholders
		a. Does current design satisfy customer requirements?
		b. Do test cases understand how to navigate through website? Anything confusing?
5.0 Closing
	5.1 Receive approval from stakeholders
	5.2 Final presentation for project
		a. Powerpoint presentation
		b. Mock-up deliverables
	5.3 Finish “Lessons Learned”

Quad Squad: Scope Statement and WBS
Students for Animals and Pets Web Development Project
Informatics 151 - Project Management, Winter 2013
State in 1-2 paragraphs how you would control for quality.  What measurements would you take in order to make a case that this project was of high quality?
List the risks involved in doing this project at each step.  Accompany each with a statement about how you would mitigate risk.

Quality:
The number one quality measurement that we are taking into consideration with our web development project is the website’s usability for our customers. It has to provide ease of use for our customers who we assume to be somewhat tech-savvy. By somewhat tech-savvy we mean that they have used free online hosting websites with pre-determined templates that they were able to work with without actual coding. In addition, we would like the learning process of manipulating information in the website to be as simple as possible. 

Another measurement that we consider is the website’s features. We would like the features to be up-to-date with the current trend in organization websites that utilize social media, chat functions, and payment methods. In addition, features such as online documentation and club information should appeal aesthetically to the viewers to possibly increase the traffic of users. 

 Lastly, tying into the measurement of ease-of-use is the website’s maintainability. Since maintenance of the website will be determined by club officers, the website should allow for future modifications. These modifications could be caused by a number of factors such as new requirements, updates, and the changing environment of the organization. We would like the website to be manageable to those with average technical skills in terms of web development, because our aim is for them to focus more on the core goals of the organization.
